How Linq code translated to sql query

LINQ Code
   ↓
Expression Tree
   ↓
EF Core Translator
   ↓
SQL Query
   ↓
Database
   ↓
C# Objects

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- IMPORTANT Performance -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

context.Users.ToList(); - Used to fetch all the data
    👉 EF Core immediately executes SQL
    👉 Loads ALL matching rows into memory
    👉 Converts them into C# objects

This is called materialization.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bad code 
var users = context.Users.ToList()
                         .Where(u => u.Age > 18);

so sql executed-  SELECT * FROM Users - since we writing ToList() before filtering
filtering happens in c# 

Note - all the users loaded in memory and filtering happening in c#
        📌 This is slow, memory-heavy, and scales badly.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Good code
var users = context.Users
                   .Where(u => u.Age > 18)
                   .ToList();

since we puts .ToList() after the filtering
so EF converts Linq -> sql as
    SELECT * FROM Users where age > 18

only requied data is fetched
Fast and efficient

